CISF to raise Special Tactics Wing for enhanced combat advantage 
7-3-2017 
NEW DELHI: The Central Industrial Security Force is raising a Special Tactics Wing (STW) in Hyderabad for tactical capacity building to have an enhanced combat and tactical advantage against the terrorists attack and other threats at vital installations in the country.Being raised on the lines of SWAT, the STW of CISF will cater to the needs of hypersensitive airports, Delhi metro and sensitive units in Naxal affected areas.The role of bomb disposal squad and quick reaction team will be focused upon in STE to counter the aircraft hijacking and other contingencies like armed attack and IED threats, said CISF Director General OP Singh. 
